    public interface TraverseprocDerived
    This is used like Traverseproc, but traverses only the slots[]-array of fooDerived-classes. This way we avoid that the traverse method of a traversable PyObject is overridden by the derived version. gc.traverse(PyObject, Visitproc, Object) takes care of exploiting both traverse methods.
